What's the issue with my account not being charged?

There could be a few reasons why your account is not being charged. It might be due to an issue with your payment method or a problem on our end. I recommend checking out our Billing Guide for more details: [Billing Guide](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/17821681919757-Billing-Guide). If you still need help, please let me know!
No problem! I'll send an email to our support team to assist you further. Please allow 2-3 days for them to investigate and get back to you.

Let's figure out why your campaign isn't spending. Could you please provide more details? For example, is this a new account or an existing one? Also, have you checked if your daily budget and bid rate are set correctly?

Thanks for the information. Here are a few things you can check to troubleshoot why your campaign isn't spending:
1. **Launch Date**: Ensure that the launch date at the ad set level is correct. Sometimes, campaigns are set to start at a later time due to Ad Manager being in PST/military time.
2. **Budget Adjustments**: During the learning phase, avoid making too many changes as it can cause fluctuations in performance. It's recommended to increase your budget no more than 50% every 2-3 days.
3. **Bid Rate**: Make sure your bid rate is competitive enough using our bid estimation tool.
For more detailed guidance, you can refer to our [tCPA Best Practices](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18020232662797-tCPA-Best-Practices).
If you've checked all these and still face issues, please let me know!
Got it! I'll send an email to our support team to assist you further with your campaign not spending. Please allow 2-3 days for them to investigate and get back to you.
